external_knowledge:
- 'identifiers' refers to the unique listing IDs;
- 'kind of properties' refers to the types of properties as represented by their names (e.g., apartment, house);
- 'where they are situated' refers to the neighborhoods where these properties are located.

sql:
SELECT listing_id, price_aprox_usd
FROM listings
ORDER BY price_aprox_usd DESC;

external_knowledge:
- "floating castles" refers to apartments in a metaphorical sense;
- "academic haven" signifies neighborhoods with good school ratings;
- "bloomed in price" is a metaphor for the price increase of the property;
- "blossomed" metaphorically refers to the time of construction or year built;
- "chariots" is a metaphor for garage spaces.

- 'Golden keys' metaphorically refers to unique identifiers (listing IDs) of properties;
- 'Treasures' symbolically represents the price of the properties;
- 'Caught the eye of over a thousand visitors' means the listings have more than 1,000 views;
- 'Top three most expensive' indicates selecting based on the highest approximate prices in USD.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM analytics
WHERE conversion_rate > 0.10;

SELECT listing_id
FROM analytics
WHERE inquiries > (SELECT AVG(inquiries) FROM analytics);
